IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText: Focus of Supplemental Report: Initial Report Narrative: On Wednesday, May 24, 2023, I S/T Garrett Dick #6158 of the Maryland State Police Criminal Enforcement Division Eastern Region received NCMEC CyberTip #161605184. The CyberTip, generated by Dropbox, Inc, indicated that a subject uploaded child pornography to the internet.The CyberTip did not record or denote a time the child pornography was uploaded by the Dropbox user account. I viewed the uploaded child pornography which depicted the following: One video approximately one (1) minutes and forty (40) seconds in length depicting a pubescent female (approximately fourteen (14) years old) wearing a blue bathing suit and white bathing suit bottoms. As the video plays the female takes her top off, exposing her breasts and utilizes her hands to manipulate her breasts. Case OPEN.

Focus of Supplemental Report: Dropbox Search Warrant Narrative: On Thursday, June 1, 2023, I S/T Garrett Dick #6158 of the Maryland State Police Criminal Enforcement Division Eastern Region authored a Dropbox search warrant on the following Dropbox, Inc account; Email: beachbum92278@gmail.com Screen/Username: Janice Righs ESP User ID: 3404743808 The search warrant was reviewed and signed by the honorable Judge Karen M. Dean of the Wicomico County Circuit Court. On Friday, June 2nd, 2023, I served the search warrant upon Dropbox, Inc via their online portal. Case OPEN, pending search warrant results.

Focus of supplemental Report: Dropbox Results Narrative: I, S/T Garrett Dick #6158 of the Maryland State Police Criminal Enforcement Division Eastern Region have previewed the Dropbox Inc results in this investigation and observed several files of potential CSAM. I will be meeting with Doctor Wehberg on 9/8/2023 to have her view the images and videos to identify the ages of the children in the videos and pictures from the Dropbox account. Case OPEN

Focus of Supplemental Report: Residential SW 103 Austin Circle Evidence: One (1) Red iPhone in red case One (1) black HP Laptop S/N: CND72653V6 One (1) white iPhone in clear case One (1) black iPhone One (1) pink iPhone SE One (1) pink iPhone model A1532 One (1) gold USB flash drive with Ejing 128GB with lightning adapter One (1) black USB flash drive with 1TB USB 3.0 printed in silver One (1) USE flash drive with MicroSD USB 2.0 printed in silver One (1) gray and silver SanDisk USB Flash Drive with lightning adapter One (1) HP Computer tower S/N: 3CR224023V with power cord One (1) silver Verbatim USB flash drive One (1) silver Attache USB flash drive 16GB One (1) silver Kingston 256MB USB flash drive One (1) blue Panasonic 256MB SD Card One (1) space gray iPad with keyboard One (1) SLOANE black and silver USB flash drive One (1) blue USB flash drive One (1) Onn. 128 GB micro SD card with adapter One (1) WYZE 32 GB black micro SD card with adapter AXON LINK: https://mdsp.evidence.com/axon/evidence?evidence_id=c041ac4190d9499790660a8509e5c9d9partner_id=5ed6a168304e40eb9a0cfb1a226ef1a1 Narrative: On Thursday, November 2, 2023, I S/T Garrett Dick #6158 of the Maryland State Police Criminal Enforcement Division Eastern Region [CEDER] accompanied by other members of CEDER executed a residential search warrant upon 103 Austin Circle, Berlin, Maryland. Matthew Powell [hereinafter referred to as Matthew] opened the front door after I made several knocks and announces. The residence was cleared by members of CEDER and the only other person present at the residence was Powells daughter identified as Kyleigh Powell [hereinafter referred to as Kyleigh]. One hundred and twenty-five (125) digital images were taken during the execution of the search warrant, and later uploaded to VeriPic in accordance with MSP policy. During the execution of the search warrant the following items were located, documented and seized; One (1) Red iPhone in red case One (1) black HP Laptop S/N: CND72653V6 One (1) white iPhone in clear case One (1) black iPhone One (1) pink iPhone SE One (1) pink iPhone model A1532 One (1) gold USB flash drive with Ejing 128GB with lightning adapter One (1) black USB flash drive with 1TB USB 3.0 printed in silver One (1) USE flash drive with MicroSD USB 2.0 printed in silver One (1) gray and silver SanDisk USB Flash Drive with lightning adapter One (1) HP Computer tower S/N: 3CR224023V with power cord One (1) silver Verbatim USB flash drive One (1) silver Attache USB flash drive 16GB One (1) silver Kingston 256MB USB flash drive One (1) blue Panasonic 256MB SD Card One (1) space gray iPad with keyboard One (1) SLOANE black and silver USB flash drive One (1) blue USB flash drive One (1) Onn. 128 GB micro SD card with adapter One (1) WYZE 32 GB black micro SD card with adapter At approximately 0611 hours [6:11 a.m.] I attempted to conduct an audibly and visually recorded interview with Matthew, however he declined to speak with me. I read Matthew the search warrant which was captured audibly and visually. At approximately 0619 hours [6:19 a.m.] I spoke with Kyleigh and read her a Maryland State Police form 78 (consent to search and seize) and explained to her that if she provides written consent, for me to preview her cell phone and verify her cellular phone contained no CSAM. Kyliegh provided written consent for me to search and preview her iPhone 11, and I did not find any CSAM on the phone. Kyleigh was immediately given her iPhone 11 back, and she left the residence. Matthew was provided copies of the search warrant, search warrant return, and inventory, and then myself and CEDER investigators exited the residence and responded to the Maryland State Police Berlin Barrack with the seized evidence which was processed and stored in accordance with MSP policy. Case OPEN.

Focus of Supplemental Report: Interview of Laura Powell AXON LINK: https://mdsp.evidence.com/axon/evidence?evidence_id=4d5de306146541ea8bbb93201e1b9df6partner_id=5ed6a168304e40eb9a0cfb1a226ef1a1 Narrative: On Monday, November 6, 2023, I S/T Garrett Dick #6158 of the Maryland State Police Criminal Enforcement Division Eastern Region conducted and audibly and visually recorded interview with Laura Powell [hereinafter referred to as Laura] concerning the investigation. The interview was conducted in the Maryland State Police Salisbury Barrack interview room. Below is a synopsis of the interview and not a transcript therefore some paraphrasing may be used; Laura was shown the Cyber-Tip and the details listed on it concerning suspect information. Laura was shown the listed suspect email address, beachbum92278@gmail.com, and advised the numbers 92278 are Matthew Powells [hereinafter referred to as Matthew]birth date. Laura was shown the Google subscriber information which listed a backup email account of: map719@gmail.com which Laura positively identified as Matthews email account. Laura also identified the email address listed by Comcast, which was MP719@comcast.net, and added that 719 is their daughtersbirth date. Laura and Matthew have been divorced since 2021, and Matthew lives with only his daughter at 103 Austin Circle, Berlin, Maryland. Laura added that Matthew has a girlfriend that may stay with him. Laura was aware of Matthew watching pornography but not child pornography. Case OPEN

Focus of Supplemental Report: Authorization of Device Search Warrant Narrative: On Thursday, December 7, 2023, I S/T Garrett Dick #6158 of the Maryland State Police Criminal Enforcement Division Eastern Region finalized the device search warrant to have the seized devices in this investigation forensically analyzed. I sent a copy of the search warrant to Assistant States Attorney Pamela Correa of the Worcester County States Attorneys Office for review. Upon completed of the search warrant review I will send the warrant to a judge and complete a supplemental report. Case OPEN.

Focus of Supplemental Report: Device Search Warrant Review Narrative: On Thursday, January 24, 2023, I S/T Garrett Dick #6158 of the Maryland State Police Criminal Enforcement Division Eastern Region sent the device search warrant to the Honorable Judge Abigail Marsh, Judge of the Wicomico County District Court for review. Upon signature of the search warrant I will complete a Digital Forensic Request to the Maryland State Police Forensic Lab and update this case, Case OPEN.
